      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $f : \\R \\to \\R$ convexe dérivable.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f : \\R \\to \\R\\)</span> convexe\ndérivable.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bb5a66d9-522b-4db4-8494-d3947b1ff685",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $p = \\lim_{x\\to+\\infty} (f(x) - xf'(x))$ existe.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(p = \\lim_{x\\to+\\infty} (f(x)\n- xf&#39;(x))\\)</span> existe.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "4d7fae7d-f7dd-4b05-af59-705a79b451d2",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Fonction décroissante sur $\\R^+$.",
        "html": "<p>Fonction décroissante sur <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\R^+\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "3b4bad5f-2d2f-46ee-b864-83632b8c1c21",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On suppose $p$ fini. En utilisant le fait que $f(x) - xf'(x)$ est\n    bornée au voisinage de $+\\infty$, montrer que $\\frac{f(x)}x$ et $f'(x)$\n    admettent une même limite $m$ finie en $+\\infty$.",
        "html": "<p>On suppose <span class=\"math inline\">\\(p\\)</span> fini. En utilisant\nle fait que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) - xf&#39;(x)\\)</span> est\nbornée au voisinage de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(+\\infty\\)</span>,\nmontrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\frac{f(x)}x\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(f&#39;(x)\\)</span> admettent une même limite <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(m\\)</span> finie en <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(+\\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5f4ab624-978d-4125-bdf8-0f44394f82e9",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$f(x) - xf'(x) = -x^2\\frac {d}{d x}\\left(\\frac {f(x)}x\\right)$.\n    Donc, $x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - p}x \\searrow$ et\n          $x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - f(0)}x \\nearrow$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) - xf&#39;(x) = -x^2\\frac {d}{d\nx}\\left(\\frac {f(x)}x\\right)\\)</span>. Donc, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - p}x \\searrow\\)</span> et\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(x \\mapsto \\frac {f(x) - f(0)}x\n\\nearrow\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "09d5e18e-5d61-47fa-9174-7b4150a5a859",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer alors que $f(x) - mx - p \\to 0$ lorsque $x\\to {+\\infty}$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer alors que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f(x) - mx - p \\to\n0\\)</span> lorsque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\to\n{+\\infty}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "f3165212-36c2-4df0-9c9d-f5cf0f015e5c",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$p\\le f(x) - mx \\le f(x) - xf'(x)$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(p\\le f(x) - mx \\le f(x) -\nxf&#39;(x)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
